  "title": "The Highest Engagement Rate Posts From Pittsburgh Small Businesses",
  "subtitle": "Ranked by engagement as a percentage of follower count, not absolute likes. The punching-above-weight list.",
  "angle": "Pittsburgh's IG posts with the strongest reach relative to their account size. Small businesses can beat national chains here.",
  "intro": "The engagement rate list doesn't care how big you are. It measures what percentage of your actual followers showed up, liked something, left a comment, watched a video. A 500,000-follower chain getting 5,000 likes is, by this math, getting ignored. A 2,800-follower coffee shop converting 39% of its audience on a giveaway post is doing something right. That's the logic behind this ranking, and it's why the top 30 is dominated by small Pittsburgh independents, not verified accounts with marketing budgets.\n\nThis quarter's leader is Delanie's Coffee in Shadyside, which hit a 39.29% engagement rate on a single honky tonk photo. Spot of Coffee, working with fewer than 3,000 followers, appears twice in the top five. Page's earned its spot at number three with a pickle split sundae that, whatever you think about the flavor combination, clearly landed.\n\nIssue 02 will expand the dataset, add more businesses to the tracking pool, and start building a picture of which Pittsburgh operators are consistently punching above their weight, not just once.",
